\begin_layout Itemize
Case III: Social and pivate values are aligned, but the high value types
 can't afford it as much as the low value types
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Hospital beds.
 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

 needs bed urgently (e.g.
 cardiac vs cosmetic surgery).
 
\begin_inset Formula $H=h>L=l$
\end_inset

.
 But no reason to assume 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

 can afford more.
 e.g.
 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{H}=y_{L}=y$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Targeting subsidized food to the poor.
 
\begin_inset Formula $H=h>L=l$
\end_inset

 but 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{H}<y_{L}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Allocating government jobs.
 Best candidates also value job the most (possibly because of private benefits!).
 But constrained in how much they can pay for the job up front.
\end_layout

